data.title: FSU's Cook leads All-ACC team

data.text:
Clemson had the most players on the Atlantic Coast Sports Media Association’s All-ACC team announced on Monday, with 15 total and nine on the first team.

Florida State running back Dalvin Cook topped every individual player on the balloting.

Cook, who leads the ACC in rushing with 1,620 yards, had 139 points to beat out two Clemson players with 131 points, wide receiver Mike Williams and linebacker Ben Boulware. FSU defensive end DeMarcus Walker of Jacksonville and Lousiville quarterback Lamar Jackson had 125 points each.

The Seminoles placed two others on the first team, offensive tackle Roderick Johnson and cornerback Tarvarus McFadden. Johnson also was announced on Monday as the winner of the ACC’s Jacobs Blocking Award as the league top offensive lineman.

FSU wide receiver Travis Rudolph and guard Kareem Are were named to the second team.

Virginia Tech wide receiver Isaiah Ford, a Trinity Christian graduated, was voted to the second team. Miami linebacker Shaquille Quarterman, an Oakleaf graduate, is an honorable mention player.
